==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heterogamous
<hw>Het`er*og"a*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <grk>ga`mos</grk> marriage: cf. F.
<ets>h⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧rogame</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot. & Biol.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The condition of having two or more kinds of flowers
which differ in regard to stamens and pistils, as in the aster.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Characterized by heterogamy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heterogamy</ent>⟦br⟧
